        <div class="history-box">
            <div class="history-icon">
                <i class="fas fa-history"></i>
            </div>
            <div class="history-content">
                <h4>The Unbreakable Cipher</h4>
                <p>For three centuries, the Vigenère cipher was known as "le chiffre indéchiffrable" (the unbreakable cipher). Its resistance to frequency analysis made it substantially more secure than previous encryption methods.</p>
                <p>The cipher was finally broken by Friedrich Kasiski in 1863 and Charles Babbage around the same time, though Babbage never published his work.</p>
                
                <h4>Usage in Wars</h4>
                <p>The Vigenère cipher was used by the Confederate States during the American Civil War, but they made critical mistakes in implementation that allowed Union cryptanalysts to decipher their messages.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
    
    <div class="lesson-section mb-5">
