                <h4>Strengths</h4>
                <ul>
                    <li>Resists simple frequency analysis (unlike the Caesar cipher)</li>
                    <li>With a very long, truly random key (one-time pad), it can be unbreakable</li>
                    <li>Multiple shift values make it significantly harder to crack than single-shift ciphers</li>
